				<td colspan="2"><span>I am soon going to save up AA points for FM, and would like to know some more details about what you need to be aware of.
<br />

<br />
I'm hoping that someone can either answer these questions that are on my mind, or provide me with a link to a topic/website that has all this info in it. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
I know, so far, that it takes 900 mana, that it wipes the aggro list of mobs, makes you go invisible and that you have to have autoattack off. And the info written above in the topic, having no pet and such.
<br />

<br />
Remaining questions:
<br />

<br />
1. Do you have to stand still to activate this? Or can you (like about anything else bards can do be on the run).
<br />
2. What is the duration/restriction of this invis? Does moving make it drop?
<br />
3. I hear this invis is not an invis vs undead. True or false? Does activating this near an undead npc mean you probably get reaggroed? Can creatures who see-invis see through it? Or is this much like the rogue's sneak-hide/shroud of stealth?
<br />
4. Do you have to be outside melee range of the mob(s) to be sure of success? And is there a need to be aware of casters who may land a spell after FM has been activated (like with monks and FD, if a spell lands after FD the mobs know the player is not dead).
<br />

<br />
I think those are most of the burning questions... if I remember any others I'll add them ;)</span></td>
